  "commentary": "With SPX at 6586.68 sitting below the 6595 GEX flip in a PIN regime, dealers are currently net buying the dip as they're long gamma and hedging short deltas. The massive 74083M gamma wall at 6600 creates a strong magnet effect, while the 185840M total GEX suggests heavy stabilization forces are in play following the detected GEX surge event. Expect dealers to aggressively sell any push toward 6595-6600 and continue buying weakness toward the 6570 negative gamma zone.\n\nKey levels: 6595 flip strike as the regime pivot, 6600 as the primary resistance/selling zone, and 6570 as the downside support where dealer buying accelerates.\n\nBottom line: expect choppy mean reversion action with upside capped near 6600.",
